The paper deals with predicting the popularity of online content on social platforms, which involves analyzing social networks and user behavior. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes a novel method using graph neural networks, which falls under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the cascading effect in information diffusion, which is a topic in cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Finally, the paper involves predicting popularity, which is a task in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
